## DNS Records

DNS stores different types of records to provide network services.

---

# A Record

Maps:

```
Domain Name → IPv4 Address
```

Example:

```
google.com → 142.x.x.x
```

---

# AAAA Record

Maps:

```
Domain Name → IPv6 Address
```

---

# CNAME Record

Creates an alias for another domain.

Example:

```
www.company.com

↓

company.com
```

---

# MX Record

Specifies the mail server responsible for receiving emails.

Example:

```
gmail.com
```

uses MX records.

